messageBody:
Hello everybody,
The Shavian alphabet had a lot longer article on Wikipedia although it seems to be less in active use than Quikscript is. I just wrote a longer article on Quickscript. It would be nice if somebody would have a look and correct my most obvious errors and remove the worst of my personal bias ;-)
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quikscript
You can make changes directly if you like (no log on needed) or let me know what's wrong.
It would also be nice to add pictures of the letters, for example, this very nice picture with new letter-names that's here on the files area. What is the copyright status of this file? Could I just add it to Wikipedia?
thanks and greetings,
Robert
